<br>
The passage opened up into a wide chamber. No, not a chamber it seemed. A depression carved into the very stone. Sound seemed to die off directly ahead of him. 'That can't be good,' he though. Staying well clear of the &quot;dead space&quot; which seemed to occupy the center of this pit. 'The Hole!' he thought, remembering a map of the fearsome dungeon that lay at the bottom of that deep pit. 'That's what it is.'<br>
<br>
A path to his right lead to the city's entrance. He had never been here, but had heard of it many times. Studying maps just in case. 'One never knew when such knowledge might be called into use.' He thought.<br>
