&quot;What?&quot; He shouted.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ohhh don't you fret.&quot; She said mockingly. &quot;He was just a pathetic light-lover. We caught him bedded with a half-breed. His death is well deserved. But he had the most beautiful emerald eyes. Pale green, almost golden in some lights. And now, you have these eyes. Very striking with your complexion. But you will never know will you? Of course they will not work with your body. To be able to see you must become Tier 'Dal.&quot;<br>
<br>
The surealness of the situation overwhelmed him. And he began to laugh. &quot;And just how does one do that?&quot;<br>
<br>
Lips were pressed to his. A soft kiss. Skeletal hands held him in place. Preventing him from pulling away. &quot;I thought you'd never ask.&quot; She whispered, her lips still touching his. She stepped away. Her footsteps . . . soft padded steps on the stone floor, leading off to his left. Hinges opening, small ones. Footsteps back to him. She took his hand, and placed a small odd shaped thing in it.<br>
<br>
He ran his thumb and forefinger over it. Exploring its contours. Metal with a stone of some sort. It seemed to have three section, the first being bulbous and larger than the others. An oblong smooth stone was set here. The second was smaller and had eight slender tendrils extending from it. Four on each side. Curved downward. Bent in kinks, it seemed. Each one ending with a needle sharp point. The last section seemed almost square, save for the small set of pincers at the end. They were closed, forming a loop. It was roughly the size of a coin. Easily fitting on the palm of his hand. An amulet. &quot;What is this?&quot; he asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;A rare thing Rogue. You are probably familiar with the mask of the deceiver, correct?&quot; she asked. Minz nodded. &quot;The mask will make one look like a Tier 'Dal. But the illusion is just that, an illusion. The wearer is still the same, as he was when the mask was donned. This amulet is wholly different. When it is worn, your body will change physically. You will no longer be the half-breed that you are. You will have the blood of the respected race coursing through your veins. You will feel things as one of the respected race. You will taste things as we do. And,&quot; she paused for effect; &quot;you will see things as we do.&quot;<br>
<br>
She took the amulet from his hand. And he heard her feeding a chain through the loop. He was dumbfounded by the entire situation. At a complete loss.<br>
<br>
Her hands were over his head.<br>
<br>
His mind whirled with the information he had taken in.<br>
<br>
The necklace slipped onto his neck.<br>
<br>
'Be a Tier 'Dal?' he thought<br>
<br>
Her slender fingers opened his shirt, allowing the amulet to rest against he bare skin. It was an odd sensation. He could swear it was moving some how.<br>
<br>
The pain shot into him like a flash. Eight needles embedding themselves deeply into his chest. He struggled to grasp at what ever it was assaulting him. But the bony hands and arms held him in check.<br>
<br>
His skin crawled.<br>
<br>
Bones cracked and protested<br>
<br>
Innards seemed to turn and shudder<br>
<br>
A moment of utter helplessness.<br>
<br>
Sight came flooding into his mind.<br>
<br>
She was there. Watching him. A grim smile of wicked satisfaction upon her lips.<br>
<br>
Something was different. He could see. But it was not the same. Things were clearer. Shadows gone. But also most of the color. As if every thing was tinted with gray.<br>
<br>
He caught sight of his hand. It was blue! Smaller and more nimble it seemed. His entire body was the blue of the tier 'dal. Skin smooth and silky to the touch. Lacking the leather quality that he had inherited from his father.<br>
<br>
And then he saw it. On his chest.<br>
<br>
A spider. Made of living steel. Sunk into his flesh. Its body flat against him. It seemed to dig into his skin. Burrowing itself into his very chest. The skin around it grafting itself to the arachnid. Its eyes stared at him in with an alien, insect stare. It wriggled slightly, settling further into his skin and bone.<br>
<br>
He shuddered visible. He could feel the spider in him. Its venom coursing through his arteries and veins. More than that, he could feel as the spider. Feeling what the spider itself felt. As if it was part of him.<br>
<br>
&quot;It is done. You are free to go.&quot; The skeleton let him go of him. &quot;Rhasine will escort you out when you are ready. <p>Minz Elandril<BR>
